    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PDU Session Modify Request Handling with Missing NAS PDU\n\n### Summary\nThe gNB NGAP module crashes when processing PDU Session Resource Modify Requests that contain items without NAS PDU content. The `ngap_gNB_handle_pdusession_modify_request` function incorrectly assumes all PDU session items will have valid NAS PDU data, leading to segmentation faults when accessing null pointers.\n\nThis issue manifests during normal 5G session management procedures when the core network sends modify requests with optional NAS payloads. The gNB process terminates unexpectedly, causing service disruption for connected UEs.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Establish a PDU session between a UE and the 5G core\n2. Trigger a PDU Session Resource Modify procedure from the AMF\n3. Send a modify request with at least one PDU session item containing NULL NAS PDU\n4. Observe segmentation fault in gNB process\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_handlers.c`: Added proper validation of NAS PDU content before processing PDU session modify items. The function now tracks valid sessions separately from total sessions and skips items with missing NAS PDU content while maintaining correct indexing.\n"
}